  "strategist": {
    "updated": "2026-06-30",
    "headline": "Full stack live \u2014 16 articles, a podcast, and 13 channels posting 7 days a week.",
    "read": "We went from three channels to the full stack. We're now syndicating 16 SEO/AEO articles across 13 connected channels \u2014 Facebook, Instagram, YouTube, Blogger, Tumblr, Telegraph, GitHub Pages, Bluesky, Mastodon, Threads, Telegram, Pinterest, plus LinkedIn via Buffer \u2014 and every channel gets unique, native copy instead of the same blurb. Facebook now posts 7 days a week and Reels run 4x/week. We also launched a podcast, 'Get Booked, Not F***ed', live on Spotify with a self-hosted RSS feed that fans out to the rest; 3 episodes are up and the vertical promo clips are wired into the social queues. Everything's still warming up, so audience numbers stay small for a few weeks \u2014 the win is that every channel is now fed with quality native content and the engagement daemons surface real ICP conversations daily.",
    "next_move": "Volume + the first real performance read. Keep the 7-day Facebook cadence and 4x/week Reels rolling, let the 16-article cluster keep fanning out across every blogging account, push the podcast (submit to Apple once their bug clears + the indie directories from the checklist), and keep mining FB/Reddit for real contractor quotes for phase-2 EEAT. First hard read comes from the Monday report \u2014 then double down on whatever archetype lands first.",
    "next_review": "2026-07-06"
  },
